h3. Problem Definition
It seems that Confluence prior to 5.9 does not have the necessary version of the Knowledge Base Plugin needed for configuring the view permissions of a Knowledgebase.

h3. Suggested Solution
This documentation will need to be updated to include that information on compatibility ;https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/use-jira-applications-and-confluence-together-427623543.html

Documentation for JIRA should be updated with this information as well.
 
h3. Note:
You can see this error in {{atlassian-jira.log}}:
{noformat}
2016-04-19 14:12:49,372 http-nio-80-exec-16 WARN citpkg 852x23535x1 6juqov 172.18.234.7 /rest/servicedesk/1/knowledgebase/permissions/IVLESTF [c.a.s.internal.applink.BaseAppLinkResponseHandlerImpl] Confluence KB plugin present but the endpoint is not. Check that the Confluence Knowledge Base plugin is at least version 2.0.5.
{noformat}

