Currently, to be able to add templates to a space, you need to be admin to that space. It would be useful to give this privilege to other users.

h4. Problem
Using Chrome Version 50.0.2661.75 m, Confluence editor will render half its height, causing UI usability problems, see the screenshot: 
[screenshot|https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/attachment/198128/Editor%20height.JPG]

Normally, the button bar would appear at the bottom of the browser, and the editor would take the full height. It works fine in Chrome 49 stable release and other browsers.

h5. Steps to reproduce
# Install Chrome Version 50.0.2661.75 m
# Open Confluence and edit a page

h4. Workaround
- Switch to Chrome stable release (version 49)
- Reference the workaround in [CONF-41035|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-41035] :Apply the following stylesheet to Confluence Admin > Custom HTML > At end of the HEAD
{code}
<style type="text/css">
#content.edit
{ display: table-cell; }
</style>
{code}
- Apply the following stylesheet using [Stylish|https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/stylish/fjnbnpbmkenffdnngjfgmeleoegfcffe] or adding to confluence global stylesheet: {code}#content.edit {
    display: table-cell;
}{code}

h4. Resolution
Use the Workaround in [CONF-41035|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-41035] to resolve this issue.

(!) Please note that Confluence supports only stable releases of browsers. For more information, refer to: [Confluence supported platforms|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/supported-platforms-207488198.html]

